UAVariable.Description: Reports the aggregated ability to move status, considering the ability to move of the Subsystem - Point and all the configured Point Machines.
Indicates the status of the basic configuration data required for the subsystem functionality.
Reports whether the point uses individual drive or common drive as cut-off principle.

Indicates the version of the EULYNX field element subsystem Requirements specification for subsystem XX which was used for development and production of the EULYNX field element subsystem. For example the EULYNX field element subsystem is developed and produced based on Requirements specification for subsystem XX version 1.6 (1.A), the fieldElementSpecificationRevision has the value "1.6 (1.A)".

Indicates whether the last time synchronisation was successful or not. This is important for the subsystem communication and diagnostic data gathering. TRUE: Current time of this subsystem is synchronised
True: The Subsystem - Point is using redrive.
Reports the last point position commanded at the point by the interlocking
Reports the movement status of the point.

Reports the ability to move status of the internal logic of the Subsystem - Point.
Reports the ability to move status of the point machine.
Index of the point machine.
True: Reaching end position of this PointMachine is a necessary condition for the point as a whole to reach a degraded end position.
The type of each point machine.
Reports the position of the point machine.
Delay of this motor starting in [sec] compared to the PointMachine that starts first when moving to the left.
delay of this motor starting in [sec] compared to the PointMachine that starts first when moving to the right
The number of started point machine movement since the last reset.
Timer that defines the maximum time period the Point has to arrive to an End position, starting with the command moving to the point machine.
Reports the position of the point
Reports the degraded point position
The time between measurements in the PointTurnEvent in [sec].

Technical Status of the system, that represents the aggregated status of all hierarchical lower systems. This allows to have a top level information on the status of the system which can be drilled down if the system is in any other state than "Ok"

Must be used by the supplier to describe the reasons for a StatusTechnical != OK, that cannot be explained by existing datapoints (NOT including IM and manufacturer specific diagnostic messages). This Information MUST be provided from the supplier. This should provide flexibility for future uses.
